          <h2 id="business-structure">Choosing Your Business Structure</h2>
          <p>Ontario hosts have three main structure options. Each has different implications for liability, taxation, administrative burden, and scalability. Here's what each one means in practice.</p>

          <h3>Sole Proprietorship</h3>
          <p>The default structure for most new hosts. You operate as an individual, report rental income on your personal T1 tax return using the T776 form, and pay personal income tax on the net profit. There's no separate business entity.</p>

