          <p>Incorporation itself requires a lawyer to draft Articles of Incorporation, a shareholders agreement, and a corporate minute book. Budget $1,500 to $3,000 for a lawyer-prepared incorporation in Ontario, or $300 to $700 for a DIY online service (though these skip the shareholders agreement and legal advice).</p>

